76
00:03:32,641 --> 00:03:33,810
Like BN for bibim naengmyeon...

77
00:03:33,811 --> 00:03:35,371
- and MN for mul naengmyeon.
- Exactly.

78
00:03:35,711 --> 00:03:36,980
- People abbreviate everything.
- Really?

79
00:03:36,981 --> 00:03:37,981
- Yes.
- Exactly.

80
00:03:37,982 --> 00:03:39,150
(I know, right?)

81
00:03:39,151 --> 00:03:41,071
You're saying they're in a reality check, right?

82
00:03:41,921 --> 00:03:43,401
- A reality check?
- A reality check?

83
00:03:43,521 --> 00:03:44,591
A reality check?

84
00:03:44,661 --> 00:03:46,160
- A reality check?
- A reality check?

85
00:03:46,161 --> 00:03:47,360
- Not a reality check.
- Come on, Tae Yong.

86
00:03:47,361 --> 00:03:48,361
A real-life couple.

87
00:03:48,631 --> 00:03:50,261
- A reality check?
- Seriously.

88
00:03:50,601 --> 00:03:52,001
Is it a reality check?

89
00:03:52,231 --> 00:03:53,360
- Gosh.
- I'm having a reality check.

90
00:03:53,361 --> 00:03:54,400
You're making me have a reality check.

91
00:03:54,401 --> 00:03:55,401
Exactly.

92
00:03:56,001 --> 00:03:58,341
- It's a reality check.
- Yes, a reality check.

93
00:03:58,771 --> 00:04:00,140
I should've said IRL.

94
00:04:00,141 --> 00:04:02,241
(Real-life couple)

95
00:04:02,671 --> 00:04:04,781
Who ended up in an IRL?

96
00:04:04,941 --> 00:04:06,711
Please stay tuned.

97
00:04:08,881 --> 00:04:12,581
(Last 1-on-1 Date: Yoon Hoo and Choi Yu Bin)

98
00:04:13,621 --> 00:04:16,221
How about we sit as we did on the first date?

99
00:04:17,261 --> 00:04:19,061
