- Hey.

525
00:22:01,691 --> 00:22:02,721
No!

526
00:22:04,621 --> 00:22:05,821
I win, right?

527
00:22:06,421 --> 00:22:08,191
- Fine, you win.
- Did I win?

528
00:22:09,431 --> 00:22:10,860
(Jae Hyuk wins Seo Yoon's ugly photo.)

529
00:22:10,861 --> 00:22:12,601
Seriously.

530
00:22:14,361 --> 00:22:15,847
How many of my photos are you getting?

531
00:22:15,871 --> 00:22:17,601
- That was fun.
- Right?

532
00:22:17,941 --> 00:22:20,941
- I meant to let you win.
- I actually thought I'd win.

533
00:22:22,241 --> 00:22:24,171
Seo Yoon entertained him.

534
00:22:24,271 --> 00:22:25,281
- Yes.
- He did.

535
00:22:26,411 --> 00:22:27,781
That was really fun.

536
00:22:27,881 --> 00:22:30,450
Thanks to you, I learned how fun...

537
00:22:30,451 --> 00:22:32,680
- You got a taste of it now, right?
- Yes, I got a taste of it.

538
00:22:32,681 --> 00:22:35,201
Don't come to a ski resort only to go sledding the entire time.

539
00:22:35,851 --> 00:22:38,091
I'll always finish the day with sledding.

540
00:22:38,221 --> 00:22:39,290
Definitely.

541
00:22:39,291 --> 00:22:42,560
(Jae Hyuk and Seo Yoon shared a fun memory at the ski slope.)

542
00:22:42,561 --> 00:22:44,360
Jae Hyuk might change his mind.

543
00:22:44,361 --> 00:22:47,700
Won't he be thinking about Eun Byul?

544
00:22:47,701 --> 00:22:49,100
- Not at all.
- He can't.

545
00:22:49,101 --> 00:22:51,130
- He can't afford to.
- Definitely not.

546
00:22:51,131 --> 00:22:52,851
He's probably thinking, "Who was Eun Byul?"

547
00:22:54,041 --> 00:22:56,210
It'd be weird if he thought about her now.

548
00:22:56,211 --> 00:22:58,540
The Final Selection is tomorrow, and...

549
00:22:58,541 --> 00:22:59,640
(Who is Jae Hyuk leaning toward?)

550
00:22:59,641 --> 00:23:01,450
- Seo Yoon is finishing strong.
- We can't predict it.

551
00:23:01,451 --> 00:23:03,691
- This is going to change things.
- That was impressive.

552
00:23:04,351 --> 00:23:08,591
(Last 1-on-1 Date: Lee Jae Seung and Cho Eun Byul)

553
00:23:08,691 --> 00:23:11,220
- There they are.
- All of a sudden...

554
00:23:11,221 --> 00:23:12,261
This couple.

555
00:23:12,461 --> 00:23:13,791
I can't wait to watch this one.

556
00:23:17,031 --> 00:23:19,001
Tomorrow is our last day. How do you feel?

557
00:23:20,631 --> 00:23:22,071
Does it feel real?

558
00:23:23,101 --> 00:23:25,001
(Nodding)

559
00:23:27,401 --> 00:23:30,971
I thought it was my last chance.

560
00:23:31,111 --> 00:23:33,780
I normally find it difficult...

561
00:23:33,781 --> 00:23:36,151
being proactive,

562
00:23:36,981 --> 00:23:38,320
but I wanted to show her...

563
00:23:38,321 --> 00:23:40,551
my effort so that I won't regret it.

564
00:23:43,251 --> 00:23:44,891
Is there anything you want to eat?

565
00:23:45,421 --> 00:23:46,461
Me?

566
00:23:47,021 --> 00:23:49,390
I like Japanese and Korean.

567
00:23:49,391 --> 00:23:50,391
I eat everything.

568
00:23:51,061 --> 00:23:52,801
Really?

569
00:23:53,901 --> 00:23:55,270
Do you not like watching movies?

570
00:23:55,271 --> 00:23:56,330
- I do.
- You do?

571
00:23:56,331 --> 00:23:57,431
Yes.

572
00:23:57,671 --> 00:23:59,501
Are you usually interested in shoes?

573
00:23:59,901 --> 00:24:01,040
Shoes?

574
00:24:01,041 --> 00:24:03,911
I'm pretty bad at styling myself.

575
00:24:05,011 --> 00:24:06,181
But you had great fashion.

576
00:24:07,081 --> 00:24:08,751
(Laughing)

577
00:24:09,781 --> 00:24:11,081
Eun Byul just laughed!

578
00:24:11,721 --> 00:24:13,880
- He's good.
- He's got it!

579
00:24:13,881 --> 00:24:15,121
He made her laugh!

580
00:24:16,421 --> 00:24:18,161
He looks very desperate.

581
00:24:18,391 --> 00:24:20,861
His lines are different now.

582
00:24:20,921 --> 00:24:23,530
He used to say, "I was like this and that,"

583
00:24:23,531 --> 00:24:24,830
but he changed the way he spoke.

584
00:24:24,831 --> 00:24:26,560
- He started focusing...
- He's asking the other person...

585
00:24:26,561 --> 00:24:29,670
- on the other person.
- more questions now.

586
00:24:29,671 --> 00:24:32,171
He's finally asking proper questions.

587
00:24:33,071 --> 00:24:35,870
That's a huge improvement for him.

588
00:24:35,871 --> 00:24:37,041
I think this will end well.

589
00:24:37,941 --> 00:24:39,010
Let's go, son.

590
00:24:39,011 --> 00:24:40,981
(Can Jae Seung win Eun Byul over?)

591
00:24:42,016 --> 00:24:43,245
I think we're here.

592
00:24:43,246 --> 00:24:45,586
(Where did they go?)

593
00:24:46,816 --> 00:24:53,156
(Baking studio: Lee Jae Seung and Cho Eun Byul)

594
00:24:53,356 --> 00:24:55,026
I used to learn at a place like this.

595
00:24:55,596 --> 00:24:56,726
You learned it before?

596
00:24:56,896 --> 00:24:57,896
Yes.

597
00:24:57,897 --> 00:24:58,925
(Eun Byul exclaiming)

598
00:24:58,926 --> 00:25:00,766
You'd be better than me, then.

599
00:25:01,766 --> 00:25:04,566
I bake as a hobby,

600
00:25:04,766 --> 00:25:06,636
and it was...

601
00:25:06,906 --> 00:25:09,476
my type of place when we arrived.

602
00:25:09,606 --> 00:25:12,246
I got excited.

603
00:25:13,346 --> 00:25:15,575
I think we're making small cakes.

604
00:25:15,576 --> 00:25:16,576
Or not.

605
00:25:17,076 --> 00:25:19,386
- Eun Byul loves baking!
- Really?

606
00:25:19,786 --> 00:25:23,215
She loves to cook and bake.

607
00:25:23,216 --> 00:25:24,855
- That's good.
- He picked the right spot.

608
00:25:24,856 --> 00:25:26,186
(Jae Seung is on a roll today.)

609
00:25:26,256 --> 00:25:27,326
I'm glad.

610
00:25:27,656 --> 00:25:28,656
- Hello.
- Hello.

611
00:25:28,657 --> 00:25:30,625
- Hello.
- Hello.

612
00:25:30,626 --> 00:25:34,025
We're going to make whipped cream cake today.

613
00:25:34,026 --> 00:25:36,235
We're going to start with the sheets...

614
00:25:36,236 --> 00:25:37,836
and decorate the top.

615
00:25:38,836 --> 00:25:40,005
- Like this?
- Yes.

616
00:25:40,006 --> 00:25:42,076
(They make the batter first.)

617
00:25:42,206 --> 00:25:44,035
Do it first, and let me know if you're tired.

618
00:25:44,036 --> 00:25:45,246
The sugar will melt.

619
00:25:45,776 --> 00:25:47,876
(Smiling)

620
00:25:53,386 --> 00:25:54,786
Let me know if your arms get tired.

621
00:25:55,686 --> 00:25:57,486
- Are you tired?
- Not yet.

622
00:26:00,356 --> 00:26:01,356
Don't your arms hurt?

623
00:26:01,856 --> 00:26:03,355
- Do you want to try it?
- No.

624
00:26:03,356 --> 00:26:05,225
(Jae Seung keeps checking on her in case she's tired.)

625
00:26:05,226 --> 00:26:06,296
Good enough?

626
00:26:06,566 --> 00:26:08,466
- Isn't it tiring?
- Not really.

627
00:26:09,236 --> 00:26:11,606
(They continue baking in harmony.)

628
00:26:13,436 --> 00:26:15,476
I never knew I'd actually bake.

629
00:26:15,736 --> 00:26:17,606
Right. But I'm glad...

630
00:26:17,936 --> 00:26:19,746
you like it.

631
00:26:21,946 --> 00:26:24,375
(Eun Byul likes to bake, )

632
00:26:24,376 --> 00:26:26,886
(so he takes it seriously.)

633
00:26:30,516 --> 00:26:31,556
- But...
- Yes?

634
00:26:31,886 --> 00:26:33,056
I feel good right now.

635
00:26:33,256 --> 00:26:34,456
- What?
- I feel good.

636
00:26:34,586 --> 00:26:36,346
- What do you mean?
- I feel so comfortable.

637
00:26:36,856 --> 00:26:38,126
It's perfect.

638
00:26:46,306 --> 00:26:48,135
He says he feels comfortable.

639
00:26:48,136 --> 00:26:51,006
- Eun Byul looks so happy.
- She looks happy to hear that.

640
00:26:51,306 --> 00:26:54,346
Jae Seung's potential is showing too late!

641
00:26:55,346 --> 00:26:57,375
- Now, let's try sifting it.
- Thank you.

642
00:26:57,376 --> 00:26:58,385
- Okay.
- Thanks.

643
00:26:58,386 --> 00:27:00,285
(They put on aprons.)

644
00:27:00,286 --> 00:27:01,446
- Aprons.
- There's one more.

645
00:27:02,816 --> 00:27:05,955
- Go, Jae Seung.
- You need to help her with it.

646
00:27:05,956 --> 00:27:07,156
Help each other out!

647
00:27:07,456 --> 00:27:08,725
Is this how you wear it?

648
00:27:08,726 --> 00:27:09,826
- I think so.
- Yes.

649
00:27:12,896 --> 00:27:15,495
(Eun Byul can't tie her apron.)

650
00:27:15,496 --> 00:27:17,965
- Go behind her.
- Jae Seung.

651
00:27:17,966 --> 00:27:19,035
- Go behind her!
- Tie it!

652
00:27:19,036 --> 00:27:21,065
- Tie it for her!
- He's going.

653
00:27:21,066 --> 00:27:22,275
- Turn.
- Jae Seung!

654
00:27:22,276 --> 00:27:24,035
- Jae Seung!
- Jae Seung!

655
00:27:24,036 --> 00:27:25,146
Can't you hear us?

656
00:27:28,376 --> 00:27:30,146
(Their cries never reached him.)

657
00:27:30,816 --> 00:27:33,546
(They ended up tying their own aprons.)

658
00:27:33,916 --> 00:27:35,086
- Did you get it?
- Yes.

659
00:27:35,586 --> 00:27:37,656
- Hey!
- Jae Seung!

660
00:27:37,716 --> 00:27:39,356
You have to tie it from behind!

661
00:27:43,296 --> 00:27:44,356
Thanks.

662
00:27:46,196 --> 00:27:47,326
Okay.

663
00:27:47,496 --> 00:27:48,535
- Good?
- Yes.

664
00:27:48,536 --> 00:27:49,596
- I'll take it.
- Okay.

665
00:27:50,796 --> 00:27:51,806
Thanks.

666
00:27:52,306 --> 00:27:53,865
How should we do it?

667
00:27:53,866 --> 00:27:57,506
(He keeps looking after her.)

668
00:27:59,976 --> 00:28:01,246
Unlike...

669
00:28:01,476 --> 00:28:04,316
on our first date,

670
00:28:04,816 --> 00:28:08,185
I could tell he was trying really hard...

671
00:28:08,186 --> 00:28:09,686
to look after me.

672
00:28:11,056 --> 00:28:12,226
Maybe get closer.

673
00:28:13,156 --> 00:28:14,226
What's this?

674
00:28:14,586 --> 00:28:17,025
(They seem much more comfortable now.)

675
00:28:17,026 --> 00:28:19,665
You know, strawberries in whipped cream.

676
00:28:19,666 --> 00:28:21,026
Isn't there a cake with that name?

677
00:28:21,696 --> 00:28:23,596
I was glad...

678
00:28:24,466 --> 00:28:26,036
that I was on a date with Eun Byul.

679
00:28:27,636 --> 00:28:30,506
(Their cake is almost done.)

680
00:28:39,546 --> 00:28:41,186
That looks good.

681
00:28:41,486 --> 00:28:42,615
How cute.

682
00:28:42,616 --> 00:28:48,085
(They worked on this cake together.)

683
00:28:48,086 --> 00:28:50,725
They don't seem awkward when they make eye contact.

684
00:28:50,726 --> 00:28:52,095
I know, right?

685
00:28:52,096 --> 00:28:53,702
They've been talking while looking down the whole time.

686
00:28:53,726 --> 00:28:57,366
- Indeed.
- You won her over, Jae Seung!

687
00:28:57,836 --> 00:28:59,435
- You're doing great!
- If he had more time...

688
00:28:59,436 --> 00:29:00,735
All his charms are starting to show!

689
00:29:00,736 --> 00:29:03,205
- He would have won over everyone.
- Seriously.

690
00:29:03,206 --> 00:29:04,576
He's in the zone.

691
00:29:04,736 --> 00:29:06,606
They give me a fuzzy feeling.

692
00:29:07,806 --> 00:29:09,716
- I wish he had more time.
- I know, right?

693
00:29:09,846 --> 00:29:10,976
He's gotten far better.

694
00:29:11,676 --> 00:29:12,786
He earned some points.

695
00:29:13,816 --> 00:29:15,185
(Last 1-on-1 Date: You Hee Dong and Park Si Woo)

696
00:29:15,186 --> 00:29:16,556
The newlyweds.

697
00:29:19,626 --> 00:29:22,295
I have a feeling we'll eat seafood.

698
00:29:22,296 --> 00:29:23,396
- Right?
- Yes.

699
00:29:23,826 --> 00:29:25,326
You're good at fishing.

700
00:29:27,296 --> 00:29:29,196
Do I look like I enjoy fishing?

701
00:29:29,496 --> 00:29:30,566
You fish well.

702
00:29:33,936 --> 00:29:35,336
When did I do that?

703
00:29:36,436 --> 00:29:37,806
You fished for me.

704
00:29:39,946 --> 00:29:42,115
It's so cute how lovey-dovey they are.

705
00:29:42,116 --> 00:29:43,576
They're really cute.

706
00:29:45,186 --> 00:29:47,415
Do you know how it feels to watch you walk by...

707
00:29:47,416 --> 00:29:50,086
when I'm waiting in the car?

708
00:29:50,856 --> 00:29:52,725
I was so...

709
00:29:52,726 --> 00:29:55,926
(She can finally laugh about it.)

710
00:29:56,196 --> 00:29:58,526
I would have chosen you if I could.

711
00:30:03,466 --> 00:30:07,736
(Where are they headed after getting closer than before?)

712
00:30:08,336 --> 00:30:11,435
(Sashimi restaurant: You Hee Dong and Park Si Woo)

713
00:30:11,436 --> 00:30:12,806
- Let's eat both.
- Both?

714
00:30:14,976 --> 00:30:15,976
What's this called?

715
00:30:17,076 --> 00:30:19,446
It's a very rare type of fish.

716
00:30:19,646 --> 00:30:21,015
Enjoy.

717
00:30:21,016 --> 00:30:22,156
- Thank you.
- Yes.

718
00:30:22,456 --> 00:30:23,516
Thank you.

719
00:30:25,186 --> 00:30:27,326
To be honest, these are...

720
00:30:28,156 --> 00:30:29,855
my favorite types of food.

721
00:30:29,856 --> 00:30:31,056
- Really?
- Yes.

722
00:30:31,256 --> 00:30:32,496
Help yourself.

723
00:30:35,236 --> 00:30:36,536
(Nodding)

724
00:30:39,766 --> 00:30:40,766
Do you eat this?

725
00:30:41,106 --> 00:30:42,206
I like it.

726
00:30:42,236 --> 00:30:43,352
Do you want me to put it in front of you?

727
00:30:43,376 --> 00:30:44,675
- You don't eat it?
- No.

728
00:30:44,676 --> 00:30:47,196
(Hee Dong moves the steamed kabocha, her favorite, toward her.)

729
00:30:47,276 --> 00:30:48,276
Do you eat this?

730
00:30:48,546 --> 00:30:49,646
- No?
- I do.

731
00:30:49,746 --> 00:30:50,816
Take this too.

732
00:30:50,916 --> 00:30:52,885
(He puts all her favorite dishes in front of her.)

733
00:30:52,886 --> 00:30:54,385
I don't think I've ever seen him...

734
00:30:54,386 --> 00:30:55,756
- Me neither.
- be so nice.

735
00:30:57,886 --> 00:30:59,026
Do you prefer the broth?

736
00:30:59,156 --> 00:31:00,356
No, the bits.

737
00:31:00,826 --> 00:31:02,456
- Is there fish inside?
- Yes.

738
00:31:02,696 --> 00:31:04,226
- Without the fish?
- No, I like fish.

739
00:31:15,536 --> 00:31:16,905
Since I came here,

740
00:31:16,906 --> 00:31:18,475
I wanted to eat raw fish...

741
00:31:18,476 --> 00:31:20,006
- at least once.
- Me too.

742
00:31:20,276 --> 00:31:21,406
I get to eat it today.

743
00:31:24,346 --> 00:31:25,786
This is so delicious.

744
00:31:26,916 --> 00:31:28,446
- She's happy.
- She is.

745
00:31:30,286 --> 00:31:31,656
(Glancing)

746
00:31:32,626 --> 00:31:34,126
Let me make one for you.

747
00:31:36,196 --> 00:31:38,156
- What will he make?
- "Let me make one for you?"

748
00:31:41,126 --> 00:31:46,136
(It may be rough around the edges, but he makes a wrap for Si Woo.)

749
00:31:48,406 --> 00:31:49,906
(Nervous)

750
00:31:52,576 --> 00:31:53,706
It's so good.

751
00:31:56,116 --> 00:31:57,116
- Are you happy?
- My gosh.

752
00:31:57,117 --> 00:31:59,045
- Is she that happy?
- She looks happy.

753
00:31:59,046 --> 00:32:01,086
- She's happy about everything.
- Yes.

754
00:32:02,586 --> 00:32:04,315
(Si Woo's reaction is so transparent.)

755
00:32:04,316 --> 00:32:05,386
It's so good.

756
00:32:05,826 --> 00:32:06,886
Really?

757
00:32:07,026 --> 00:32:10,756
(Hee Dong avoids eye contact for no reason.)

758
00:32:13,466 --> 00:32:14,926
- What is it?
- Nothing.

759
00:32:15,336 --> 00:32:17,066
- Why do you keep smiling?
- It's nothing.

760
00:32:17,636 --> 00:32:22,106
Looking at Si Woo enjoying it...

761
00:32:22,336 --> 00:32:23,776
made me very happy too.

762
00:32:32,316 --> 00:32:34,116
I talked about this a lot.

763
00:32:34,916 --> 00:32:35,986
About what?

764
00:32:38,726 --> 00:32:41,386
About eating raw fish with the person I like.

765
00:32:43,056 --> 00:32:45,866
- Really?
- Yes, I talked about it a lot.

766
00:32:51,196 --> 00:32:52,466
That sentence is unforgettable.

767
00:32:53,436 --> 00:32:54,766
It made my heart race.

768
00:32:57,306 --> 00:33:02,575
(By expressing their thoughts without hiding, )

769
00:33:02,576 --> 00:33:07,516
(they grow closer on the last night.)

770
00:33:09,086 --> 00:33:10,516
The person she likes.

771
00:33:10,656 --> 00:33:11,855
It means she likes him.

772
00:33:11,856 --> 00:33:13,696
- That's right.
- Yes, it means she likes him.

773
00:33:13,786 --> 00:33:17,055
- Si Woo is more assertive here.
- She doesn't hesitate at all now.

774
00:33:17,056 --> 00:33:18,555
Si Woo is assertive.

775
00:33:18,556 --> 00:33:20,642
(How will the rest of the date pan out for Si Woo and Hee Dong?)

776
00:33:20,666 --> 00:33:23,195
(Shin Jae Hyuk and Woo Seo Yoon, a ski resort food court)

777
00:33:23,196 --> 00:33:25,466
- Let's eat. Finally.
- Finally.

778
00:33:25,866 --> 00:33:27,836
Choose all you want. It's on me.

779
00:33:29,876 --> 00:33:31,575
- Shall we sit here?
- Yes, let's sit here.

780
00:33:31,576 --> 00:33:34,606
(They ordered their food.)

781
00:33:36,546 --> 00:33:39,046
I thought we wouldn't get to talk today.

782
00:33:40,486 --> 00:33:42,646
- Talk... Really?
- I thought we wouldn't get to talk.

783
00:33:43,116 --> 00:33:45,256
I'm glad we can. At least for me.

784
00:33:48,486 --> 00:33:50,156
Other than talking,

785
00:33:50,796 --> 00:33:52,966
- we snowboarded too.
- We snowboarded too.

786
00:33:53,266 --> 00:33:55,436
- We snowboarded too.
